ngAnimate also allows for animations to be consumed by JavaScript code. The approach is similar to CSS-based animations (where there is a shared CSS class that is referenced in our HTML code) but in addition we need to register the JavaScript animation on the module. By making use of the module.animation() module function we can register the animation.
trans-unit.target: ngAnimate를 사용하면 JavaScript 코드에서 애니메이션을 사용할 수도 있습니다. 이 접근 방식은 CSS 기반 애니메이션 (HTML 코드에서 참조되는 공유 CSS 클래스가있는 곳)과 유사하지만 또한 모듈에 JavaScript 애니메이션을 등록해야합니다. 의 사용함으로써 module.animation() 모듈 기능 우리는 애니메이션을 등록 할 수있다.

trans-unit.source: one-way binding does not copy the value from the parent to the isolate scope, it simply sets the same value. That means if your bound value is an object, changes to its properties in the isolated scope will be reflected in the parent scope (because both reference the same object).
trans-unit.target: 단방향 바인딩은 상위에서 분리 범위로 값을 복사하지 않고 단순히 동일한 값을 설정합니다. 즉, 바인딩 된 값이 개체 인 경우 격리 된 범위의 속성 변경 내용이 부모 범위에 반영됩니다 (둘 다 동일한 개체를 참조하므로).

trans-unit.source: one-way binding watches changes to the identity of the parent value. That means the $watch on the parent value only fires if the reference to the value has changed. In most cases, this should not be of concern, but can be important to know if you one-way bind to an object, and then replace that object in the isolated scope. If you now change a property of the object in your parent scope, the change will not be propagated to the isolated scope, because the identity of the object on the parent scope has not changed. Instead you must assign a new object.
